  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the extended type itself to be able to implement a comparator on the simulation time.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, StationInterface, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducerInterface

    public class Schedule<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>
extends Generator<A,R,T>
    The schedule is an extension to the generate which accepts a schedule of interarrival times. Instead of generating with a continuous interarrival distribution we submit a map consiting of keys (execution times). Each key indicates the starting time of a new interval, while the value in the map is the continuous distribution function to use to draw the interarrival times. If no values have to be generated in a certain interval, use a large interarrival time value in the distribution function, or use DistConstant(stream, 1E20) to indicate that the next drawing will take place after the end of the interval.
